
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `firefox` baraye baz kardan web browser Firefox az terminal estefade mishavad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `firefox &`  --> 🌐 Firefox ra dar paszamine (background) baz kon va terminal ra azad negah dar.
    🔹 `firefox -new-window <url>` --> ➕ Yek panjere jadid Firefox ba address dade shode baz kon.
    🔹 `firefox -private-window <url>` --> 🕶️ Yek panjere khososi (private) jadid Firefox ba address dade shode baz kon.
    🔹 `firefox -P <profile>` --> 👤 Firefox ra ba profile moshakhas shode baz kon.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ firefox

    🔹 Firefox ra baz mikonad.

    $ firefox https://www.google.com

    🔹 Firefox ra baz mikonad va safhe Google ra namayesh midahad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ firefox -new-window https://www.example.com

    🔹 Yek panjere jadid dar Firefox baz mishavad va address https://www.example.com ra load mikonad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `firefox` command is used to launch the Firefox web browser from the terminal.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `firefox &`  --> 🌐 Launch Firefox in the background and free up the terminal.
    🔹 `firefox -new-window <url>` --> ➕ Open a new Firefox window with the specified URL.
    🔹 `firefox -private-window <url>` --> 🕶️ Open a new Firefox private window with the specified URL.
    🔹 `firefox -P <profile>` --> 👤 Launch Firefox with the specified profile.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ firefox

    🔹 Launches Firefox.

    $ firefox https://www.google.com

    🔹 Launches Firefox and displays the Google webpage.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ firefox -new-window https://www.example.com

    🔹 Opens a new window in Firefox and loads the URL https://www.example.com.
